            "creation_date": 1399624913,
            "body": "<p>Make a class hirarchy. Define a super class contains length and width; have it implement Comparable and pass in the super class to do only comparison of length and width; then subclass to get your A and B class so that you don't compare the width/height by default.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 23560190,
            "question_id": 23560146
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/p5Q02.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 2103622,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1870555,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1870555/christopher",
                "reputation": 27446,
                "display_name": "christopher",
                "accept_rate": 75
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1399625192,
            "creation_date": 1399625192,
            "body": "<p>First, you define a superclass <code>A<\/code>.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public class A {\n    private int length;\n\n    public A(int length) {\n       this.length = length'\n    }\n\n    public int getLength() { return length; }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>And create two classes that subclass this, <code>B<\/code> and <code>C<\/code>.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public class B extends A { \n    public B(int length) {\n       super(length);\n    }\n}\n\npublic class C extends A { \n    public B(int length) {\n       super(length);\n    }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>And now you can create a method entitled:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public void compare(A first, A second) {\n    if(first.getLength() &gt; second.getLength()) {\n         // Do something..\n    }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>And this can be called as follows:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>A b = new B(5);\n\nA c = new C(6);\n\ncompare(b, c);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 23560275,
